ğŸ—ï¸DOCUMENT OBJECT MODEL (DOM)

âœ”ï¸ Document - file
âœ”ï¸ Object - tagelements
âœ”ï¸ Model - layer structure 

âœ”ï¸ DOM represents the content of an XML or HTML document as a tree structure.
âœ”ï¸ Programming interface or an API.
âœ”ï¸ Easily read,access and update the content of the document.
âœ”ï¸ Object-Oriented representation of the web page.It can be modified with a scripting languages such as javascript.


âœ”ï¸ All HTML elements can be accessed through the XML DOM.

ğŸ“Œ MARKUP TEST : 

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<meta charset="utf-8">
<title>Page Title</title>
<body>
   <h1>This is a Heading</h1>
   <p>This is a paragraph.</p>
   <p>This is another paragraph.</p>
</body>
</html>


ğŸ“Œ DOCUMENT OBJECT MODEL (DOM) :

|-DOCTYPE: html
|-HTML lang="en"
 |--HEAD
 | |----META charset="utf-8"
 | |----#text:
 | |----TITLE
 | |------#text: Page Title
 | |----#text:
 |-BODY
   |--#text:
   |--H1
   | |----#text: This is a Heading
   |--#text:
   |--P
   | |----#text: This is a paragraph.
   |--#text:
   |--P
   | |----#text: This is another paragraph.
   |--#text:
